Pin note: v0.8.0 ships the badges generator. skillcard.badges maps a card.json
to shields.io endpoint JSON (one badge per metric: scan, trigger, tasks, signed,
card), and `skillcard badges <skill-dir> --metric all --out DIR` writes one
<metric>.json per badge into a dir OUTSIDE the skill source — the --out guard
refuses an in-source target, so no card content_hash moves. The v0.7.1 -> v0.8.0
diff touches only skillcard/badges.py, skillcard/cli.py, and skillcard/__init__.py
(plus the pyproject version bump); hashing.py / build_card.py / render.py / schema
are unchanged, so this re-vendor moves no card content_hash. This vendored copy is
byte-identical to the v0.8.0 tag with no cabinet-local deviation.

This is a pinned copy of Califa's `schema/` + `skillcard/` packages (including
the `skillcard.harness` subpackage, dormant here — `make check` never runs
`skillcard eval`), plus the Jinja template and pyproject, so the public
cabinet's `make check` can validate and gate skill cards without a private-repo
CI secret. v0.8.0 additionally enables `skillcard badges`, consumed by the
badge-serving CI job (.github/workflows/badges.yml).

